* In the 13th year of the Enryaku era ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|zh|儒略曆|fr|Calendrier_julien|es|Calendario_juliano|12=draft|12=draft}} [[794]] {{ill|December 4|ja|12月4日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Emperor Kanmu issued an edict renaming Yamashiro Province and declared the new capital to be Heian-kyō. By this edict, the site of the former Ōtsu Palace in Omi Province was also restored as the city of Ōtsu.
* In the 6th year of the Kan'ei era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|公历|fr|Calendrier_grégorien|es|Calendario_gregoriano|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1629]] {{ill|December 22|ja|12月22日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – During the Shii Incident, Emperor Go-Suido abdicated in favor of his 7‑year‑old second daughter, Princess Kōko (later known as Emperor Meisei).

== Births ==


== Deaths ==
* In the 13th year of the Eishō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|公历|fr|Calendrier_grégorien|es|Calendario_gregoriano|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1516]] {{ill|December 1|ja|12月1日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Utsunomiya Naritsuna, a Sengoku daimyo and the 17th head of the Utsunomiya clan of Shimotsuke Province, regarded as the restorer of the Utsunomiya clan (born 1468).

