{{Lunisolar November}}
'''November 8''' is the 8th day of the month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, and the day is designated as {{ill|Shakkō|ja|赤口|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.

== Events ==
* In the 13th year of the Enryaku era ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|en|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|zh|儒略曆|fr|Calendrier_julien|es|Calendario_juliano|12=draft|12=draft}} [[794]] {{ill|December 4|ja|12月4日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Emperor Kanmu issued an edict renaming Yamashiro Province and declared the new capital to be Heian-kyō. By this edict, the site of the former Ōtsu Palace in Omi Province was also restored as the city of Ōtsu.
* In the 6th year of the Kan'ei era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|en|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|公历|fr|Calendrier_grégorien|es|Calendario_gregoriano|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1629]] {{ill|December 22|ja|12月22日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – During the Shii Incident, Emperor Go-Suido abdicated in favor of his 7‑year‑old second daughter, Princess Kōko (later known as Emperor Meisei).

== Births ==


== Deaths ==
* In the 13th year of the Eishō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|en|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|公历|fr|Calendrier_grégorien|es|Calendario_gregoriano|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1516]] {{ill|December 1|ja|12月1日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Utsunomiya Naritsuna, a Sengoku daimyo and the 17th head of the Utsunomiya clan of Shimotsuke Province, regarded as the restorer of the Utsunomiya clan (born 1468).

