'''November 8''' is the 8th day of the month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/November (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}}, and the day is designated as {{ill|Shakkō|ja|赤口|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shakkō|1=Shakkō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11635368}}.

== Events ==
* In the 13th year of the Enryaku era ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|794|en|794|WD=Q30887|lt=794|1=794}} {{ill|December 4|en|December 4|WD=Q2310|lt=December 4|1=December 4}}) – Emperor Kanmu issued an edict renaming Yamashiro Province and declared the new capital to be Heian-kyō. By this edict, the site of the former Ōtsu Palace in Ōmi Province was also restored as the city of Ōtsu.
* In the 6th year of the Kan'ei era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1629|en|1629|WD=Q6847|lt=1629|1=1629}} {{ill|December 22|en|December 22|WD=Q2636|lt=December 22|1=December 22}}) – During the Shii Incident, Emperor Go-Suido abdicated in favor of his 7-year-old second daughter, Princess Kōko (later known as Emperor Meisei).

== Births ==

== Deaths ==
* In the 13th year of the Eishō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1516|en|1516|WD=Q6212|lt=1516|1=1516}} {{ill|December 1|en|December 1|WD=Q2297|lt=December 1|1=December 1}}) – Utsunomiya Naritsuna, a Sengoku daimyo and the 17th head of the Utsunomiya clan of Shimotsuke Province, regarded as the restorer of the Utsunomiya clan (born 1468).

